          <h2 id="section2">Important Factors When Choosing an Elevator Partner</h2>

          <h3 style="font-size: 1.15em; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px;">Proven Quality and Compliance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Ensure the partner adheres to Indian safety codes, BIS standards, and international certifications.</li>
            <li>Confirm the use of durable materials and state-of-the-art manufacturing that withstands India’s diverse climate and high usage demands.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="font-size: 1.15em; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px;">Technological Innovation and Customization</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Look for companies offering the latest smart elevator technologies such as IoT integration, AI-based predictive maintenance, touchless controls, and energy-efficient regenerative drives.</li>
            <li>Ability to customize cabin design, controls, and capacity based on project-specific architectural and demand needs is essential for premium projects.</li>
            </ul>

          <h3 style="font-size: 1.15em; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px;">Comprehensive After-Sales Support</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A responsive and extensive service network across India guarantees fast maintenance and minimal downtime.</li>
            <li>Availability of long-term service contracts, remote monitoring, and timely spare parts supply is crucial for lifecycle management.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 style="font-size: 1.15em; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px;">Experience in Diverse Projects</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Prefer partners with a track record in handling projects similar in scale and type—luxury residences, commercial complexes, hospitals, or industrial buildings.</li>
            <li>Experience ensures smooth project execution, regulatory approvals, and ability to address unique technical challenges.</li>
            </ul>

          <h3 style="font-size: 1.15em; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 15px;">Strong Financial Stability and Partnerships</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>A financially robust partner is likely to invest continuously in R&D and expansion to support clients.</li>
            <li>Leading elevator companies often collaborate with global technology providers, giving access to cutting-edge innovations.</li>
          </ul>

